The paper involves the application of Fuzzy Markup Language (FML) to construct an FML-based Dynamic Assessment Agent (FDAA) for the game of Go. This involves an intelligent decision-making and learning mechanism, an intelligent game bot, a proximal development agent, and an intelligent agent. The paper also presents an FML-based Human–Machine Cooperative System (FHMCS) for the game of Go. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also involves game theory and human-computer interaction, which makes cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) and cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) likely sub-categories. Additionally, the paper involves natural language processing for player performance evaluation and linguistic descriptions for game results commentary, which makes cs.CL (Computation and Language) a likely sub-category.
